pr_body:
Bumps [omniauth](https://github.com/omniauth/omniauth) from 1.9.1 to 2.1.0.
Release notes

Sourced from omniauth's releases.

v2.1.0

This release adds Ruby 3.0+ support.

Due to kwarg changes in ruby 3, we have bumped the minimum required version of Rack to 2.2.3, which is where ruby3 support was added.

Releasing as a minor as dependency resolution should fail at install if an application is locked to a rack below new minimum.

Full Changelog: https://github.com/omniauth/omniauth/compare/v2.0.4...v2.1.0

v2.0.4

This release removes unnecessary warning logging when accessing GET routes that are not related to the OmniAuth request path.

Thanks to @‚Äãcharlie-wasp and @‚Äãsponomarev at Evil Martians for the bug find and subsequent PR.

Fix rescuing of application errors when call_app! is used.

As a consequence of the changes that were merged in #689, errors thrown by strategies that utilize other_phase (or more specifically call_app!), would be caught by omniauth, causing headaches for folks looking to have those errors handled by their application. This should allow for errors that come from the app to pass through, while passing errors that come from the authentication phases to the fail! handler.

Resolves #1030

Fix for incorrect order of request_validation_phase in test_mode.

@‚Äãjsdalton gave an awesome report of the issue present in test_mode in #1033

The current implementation of mock_call was verifying the token for all requests, regardless of whether the current path is on the omniauth request path. The change was introduced recently in 1b784ff. See #1032 for details.

This creates two problems:

  1. When test mode is on, the authenticity verification logic is run inappropriately against requests where this may not even be wanted.
  2. The behavior varies from actual production behavior, potentially allowing bugs to be introduced by unwary developers.

Note that this bug was only present when OmniAuth was configured for test_mode and using the mock_call phases.

Allow passing rack-protection configuration to default request_validation_phase

This release now properly allows an instance of OmniAuth::AuthenticityTokenProtection (with passed in rack-protection configuration) to be used as the request_validation_phase.

Thanks @‚Äãjkowens #1027

If you haven't already read the release notes for v2.0.0, you should do so.

v2.0.0

Version 2.0 of OmniAuth includes some changes that may be breaking depending on how you use OmniAuth in your app.

Many thanks to the folks who contributed in code and discussion for these changes.

OmniAuth now defaults to only POST as the allowed request_phase method.

Hopefully, you were already doing this as a result of the warnings due to CVE-2015-9284.

... (truncated)

pr_title: Feature: Support multiple mentors for groups
pr_body:
Closes #2050 

#### Describe the changes you have made in this PR -
- Model changes:
  - Renamed `mentor` to `owner` in Group
  - Added mentor column (boolean) to GroupMember (default=false). Owner need not be added as mentor
  
- Controller changes:
  - Modified GroupMemberController.update method to allow setting and unsetting mentors by owner

- Policy changes:
  - Allow mentors to grade, CRUD, and reopen assignments
  -  Only the owner is allowed to set/unset mentors and add/remove members in Group

- Fixed App specs
- Fixed API specs
- Wrote specs
- Added feature to API
- Added translation

#### Need help with view design for group#show

**Owner view:**
![Screenshot from 2022-06-21 21-43-00](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/76901313/174847736-fa1a2706-7072-41b9-9809-d8892e2b6522.png)

**Mentor View:**
![Screenshot from 2022-06-21 21-43-18](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/76901313/174847726-b36fb375-88d4-49a9-bb38-3992eda4b112.png)


Note: Please check **Allow edits from maintainers.** if you would like us to assist in the PR.

pr_body:
Fixes #1892 

#### Describe the changes you have made in this PR -

- added new column `feature_restrictions` in `assignment` table of type `jsonb` with default `{}`
- added `restrictedFeature.js` will be used to display the checkbox in the assignment form.
- added a hidden field that appends the selected elements into form submission.
- added feature_restrictions in `params.permit`
- if the project has a restriction of 'add collaborators' or 'copy/paste' the link will have `display:none`
- if the project has a restriction of 'Verilog' or 'Combinational analysis tool' the link will have `display:none` in the simulator navbar. 

## Screenshot

1. Enable-Feature Restriction
![Screenshot from 2022-07-19 19-03-33](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/76901313/179763397-23b982ba-a530-4b15-801c-bc58a4252e50.png)

2. Feature-Restrictions Section in Assignment
![Screenshot from 2022-07-19 19-04-58](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/76901313/179763581-a9071504-14de-42a5-993f-6fd0770caa7c.png)

> Copy / Paste,Allow Collaborators is restricted hence the buttons are not being rendered in the Page.



Note: Please check **Allow edits from maintainers.** if you would like us to assist in the PR.

pr_body:
Fixes #2321 

#### Describe the changes you have made in this PR -

- [x] Added noticed gem.
- [x] Config DB, Routes, Model.
- [x] Added notification for:
      - Star a Project.
      - Fork a Project.
- [x] UI
- [ ] Activity_notification Remove

## UI
- Notification Page
![Screenshot from 2022-07-29 22-09-37](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/76901313/181805605-3d0047b9-dfc0-47d9-9c98-4e8599d75b74.png)


- Navbar Quick Notifications
![Screenshot from 2022-08-10 10-56-31](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/76901313/183823136-080d0274-ee80-40cb-8e5e-d217a3174c2a.png)


Note: Please check **Allow edits from maintainers.** if you would like us to assist in the PR.

Fixes #3290 

#### Describe the changes you have made in this PR -
- Added `slim-select` dependencies for multiple select options.
- Suggested Tags are generated from:
  - Circuit Elements Used
  - Circuit Name

Note: Please check **Allow edits from maintainers.** if you would like us to assist in the PR.
